I've found comprehensive information about Biome 2.x nursery rules and linter strict configuration. Here are the key findings:

## Nursery Rules in Biome 2.x

Nursery rules require explicit opt-in via configuration on stable versions because they may still have bugs or performance problems (even if they are marked as recommended). They are enabled by default on nightly builds, but as they are unstable their diagnostic severity may be set to either error or warning, depending on whether we intend for the rule to be recommended or not when it eventually gets stabilized.

Nursery rules get promoted to other groups once they become stable or may be removed.

## Configuration

Nursery is a group of new rules that are still under development. Nursery rules require explicit opt-in via configuration on stable versions because they may still have bugs or performance problems (even if they are marked as recommended).

To enable nursery rules in your Biome configuration, you can use the following structure:

```json
{
  "linter": {
    "rules": {
      "nursery": {
        "preset": "all"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Or enable specific nursery rules individually with severity levels like `"error"` or `"warn"`.

## Strict Configuration

More and more plugins seem to provide also a strict and/or a stylistic presets. This indicates that Biome supports different preset levels for configuring rule strictness in your linting configuration.


